Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I go to Page 04 of Thoracic CT

When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Trachea' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Tracheal deviation' radio button is enabled
And 'Tracheal stenosis' radio button is enabled
And 'Tracheomalacia' radio button is enabled
And 'Mass' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Tracheal deviation' radio button
Then 'Right' radio button is enabled
And 'Left' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Tracheal stenosis' radio button
Then 'Height in relation to vertebral bodies' dropdown menu is enabled
And 'Min. diameter axial' input field is enabled
And 'Min. diameter craniocaudal' input field is enabled

When I select 'Tracheomalacia' radio button
Then 'Collapse in expiration' checkbox is enabled
And 'Suspected' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Mass' radio button
Then 'Maximum diameter' input field is enabled
And 'Benign lesion, not further specified' radio button is enabled
And 'Malignant lesion, not further specified' radio button is enabled
And 'Dignity unclear' radio button is enabled
And 'Polyp' radio button is enabled
And 'Papillomatosis' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Benign lesion, not further specified' radio button
Then 'Suspected' checkbox is enabled
When I select 'Malignant lesion, not further specified' radio button
Then 'Suspected' checkbox is enabled
When I select 'Dignity unclear' radio button
Then 'Suspected' checkbox is enabled
When I select 'Polyp' radio button
Then 'Suspected' checkbox is enabled
When I select 'Papillomatosis' radio button
Then 'Suspected' checkbox is enabled
